It occurs when we give some wrong argument type to a function.

Date class takes Date as arguments in the format 

yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm:ss    or
yyyy/MM/dd 

if yyyy-MM-dd or anything other than the slash (/) is provided, It gives an Illegal Argument Exception.


Resolution - 

Use SimpleDateFormat instead.

SimpleDateFormat dateFormat = new SimpleDateFormat("dd-MM-yyyy");
Date date1 = dateFormat.parse("11-10-2017");
